<FIRST>r a PM-AP-Bismarck     04-12 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP-Bismarck,0143</SECOND>
<HEAD>AP Names Phyllis Mensing Correspondent In Bismarck</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BISMARCK, N.D. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Phyllis Mensing, day supervising editor in
the Chicago bureau of The Associated Press, has been named
correspondent in charge of the AP's Bismarck bureau.
   The appointment was announced Tuesday by Tena Haraldson, chief
of bureau for North Dakota and South Dakota.
   Mensing, 39, joined the AP as a part-time newswoman while
attending school at Augustana College in Sioux Falls, S.D.
Following graduation and a year teaching, she rejoined the AP in
Sioux Falls in 1972. Other assignments took her to Pierre, S.D.,
Minneapolis, Fargo, N.D. _ where she served as correspondent _ and
Philadelphia.
   Mensing is a native of Mapleton, Minn.
   She succeeds Philip Brasher, who will transfer to the AP's
Washington bureau to be a regional reporter for Minnesota, North
Dakota and South Dakota.
</TEXT>
