<FIRST>r a PM-AP-Indianapolis     04-12 0097</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP-Indianapolis,0100</SECOND>
<HEAD>AP Names News Editor For Indiana</HEAD>
<DATELINE>INDIANAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Susan Huddleston, day supervisor in the
Indianapolis bureau of The Associated Press, has been named news
editor for Indiana.
   The appointment was announced Tuesday by Indianapolis Chief of
Bureau Robert Shaw.
   Huddleston succeeds Lindel Hutson, who recently was named chief
of bureau in Oklahoma City.
   Huddleston, 32, is a native of Limestone, Maine, and a graduate
of Centre College of Kentucky. She worked for The
Commonwealth-Journal of Somerset, Ky., before joining the AP in
Frankfort, Ky., in 1984. She transferred to Indianapolis later that
year.
</TEXT>
