<HEAD>Tokyo's Population Declines for Second Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The city's population has declined for the second
consecutive year, apparently because of high real estate prices in
the capital.
   Tokyo's population as of Jan. 1 was 11,718,720, down by 21,641
from a year earlier, the metropolitan government announced Tuesday.
   The National Land Agency says the average land price in Tokyo is
$630 a square foot. In neighboring areas, the average price ranges
from $180 to 255 a square foot.
</TEXT>
