responsibility for major sports negotiations until his planned
retirement next year.
   NBC's Olympic telecasts from Seoul received lower-than-projected
ratings, and its aggressive news coverage of the event alienated
some Korean and U.S. viewers. But NBC swept the prime-time ratings
and made an estimated profit of $80 million.
   Watson's move was announced one day after NBC won 12 Sports Emmy
Awards, more than any other network.
