<HEAD>Government Bank Subsidizes Loan Against Foreign Competition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government's Export-Import Bank is lending
$17 million to an American firm at 6.5 percent to help a Louisiana
paper mill compete with a foreign mill receiving such favorable
financing.
   Babcock and Wilcox will use the money to install a heat recovery
boiler at a Gaylord Container Corp. paper mill at Bogalusa, La.,
the bank said Tuesday. The loan was announced after the government
determined that the Brazilian government had offered a 6.5 percent
``noncompetitive'' loan to Gotaverken, a joint venture of Brazilian
and Swedish companies.
