<HEAD>New Orleans' Own Honored on Official Jazz Fest Poster</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The New Orleans Jazz and Heritage Festival's
jazzy 1989 poster can't get enough of Fats Domino.
   A smiling Domino is shown in four identical 1960s portraits
tinted in four colors.
   ``That's just fine,'' the 62-year-old New Orleans native said of
the 20th anniversary poster. ``It represents when I was young and I
like that about it.''
   The poster, unveiled Tuesday, was done by New Orleans artist
Richard Thomas.
   ``They told me they either wanted Louis Armstrong or Fats Domino
and I said `Let's do Fats,''' Thomas said. ``I love them both, but
people always kid me about how much I look like Fats.''
   Domino, who said he works five to six months a year now, will
play May 7 at this year's jazzfest.
   ``All I need is a good piano and a good mike and I'm happy,''
the singer said.
