<HEAD>Archaeological Sites Close For A Day Because of Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 300 striking Culture Ministry
employees today barred hundreds of tourists from visiting ancient
ruins atop Acropolis hill.
   The one-day strike closed historical sites and state-run museums
nationwide as guards, archaeologists, tour guides and other
employees walked off their jobs for higher pay and more funds for
care of ancient monuments.
   ``Bad working conditions, low salaries and continuous personnel
changes are some of the reasons monuments are not satisfactorily
protected and why we are on strike,'' the employee union said in a
statement.
