<DATELINE>VARESE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six Soviet rock musicians asked for
political asylum in Italy just before they were to board a flight
to Moscow, officials said today.
   Dimitri Kusanetsov, 26; Evgeni Arnautov, 31; Valeri Kot, 26;
Sergei Antimonov, 28; Vadim Galitsyn, 25; and Lilia Vinogradova,
21, of the Moscow band Pilgrim arrived in Italy on April 2.
