<FILEID>AP-NR-04-12-89 1115EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i PM-Mexico-Killings     04-12 0181</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Mexico-Killings,0191</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mexican Police Arrest Suspected Serial Killer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police have arrested a man suspected of
killing nine transients in a series of shootings that have
terrorized the city of Guadalajara, the government news agency
Notimex reported.
   The arrest Tuesday capped an investigation involving thousands
of federal and state police who searched the city looking for the
killer.
   Authorities dubbed the killer the ``Maniac 7.65'' after the type
of pistol used in the killings, which all occurred on the city's
streets.
   After slaying one transient, the assailant wrote ``He's dead''
on the pavement and drew an arrow pointing toward the body.
   Police said they knew of no motive for the killings.
   Notimex, citing a police statement, said Jalisco state police
arrested Mario Perez, 35, in a Guadalajara hotel late Tuesday.
   Police seized a car belonging to Perez, which they said had
recently been painted a different color in an attempt to elude
authorities, Notimex said. They also seized the pistol they believe
was used in the killings.
   Authorities told Notimex they suspect Perez is the serial killer.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
