<HEAD>Three Family Members Stabbed to Death; Pregnant Mother Wounded</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with mother dying, new charges expected.
No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 34-year-old man stabbed to death a family
of four, including two toddlers and an expectant mother, police
said today.
   Newton Carlton Slawson of Plant City was arrested and charged
with murder, manslaughter and attempted murder before the mother
died at a hospital this morning, said police spokesman Steve Cole.
The charges were expected to be updated with her death.
   Peggy Williams Wood, 21, had been eight months pregnant; the
fetus died at the time of the slayings, police said.
   ``No clear-cut motive has been established,'' Cole said.
   ``Apparently he knows the family and has visited them before,''
the spokesman said.
   Police found the bodies of Gerald A. Wood, 23, his daughter
Jennifer, 4, and son, Glendon, 3, at their apartment Tuesday night,
Cole said.
   ``The mother was able to crawl down a back staircase and next
door to a relative's home to summon help. She had been stabbed and
was bleeding severely,'' Cole said.
   A description of a car seen leaving the scene was broadcast on
police radio, and an officer finishing an off-duty job at a food
store spotted it 45 minutes after the killings and arrested
Slawson, Cole said.

