Rose Garden, and Bush escorted Robinson over to demonstrate his
skill. ``Now this may not be regulation,'' Bush said as Robinson
sighted on the basket, removed is coat, and lofted the ball in.
   Next it was Bush's turn. He sank his free throw the first try.
   Michigan Coach Steve Fisher on behalf of the university's
basketball staff gave Bush a ``Michigan No. 1'' jersey.
   ``I think the pride that surrounds this city and White House is
indicative of what all of us strive for, to be champions and to be
number one,'' Fisher told reporters after the ceremony. ``We feel
fortunate, but proud, that the hard effort and work that we put in
allowed us to be here.''
