<TEXT>
   Two Englishmen shared first place in the sixth
annual Arthur Rubinstein International Piano Master Competition in
Tel Aviv.
   Benjamin Frith, 31, and Ian Fountain, 19, were chosen late
Tuesday by a 12-member international jury after two weeks of
competition among 43 pianists.
   Jury president Zvi Avni said the panel decided to award two
first-place prizes because ``we were very impressed by both these
men at different stages of the competition.''
   ``They have both shown a great technique and each one of them
has a special musical personality that has a potential for a great
career and international importance.''
