home state, hey, what's wrong with that?
   And the super collider decision was made by President Reagan.
   It's a good decision.
   I want to support it.
   The space center was made by _ I guess, when President Johnson
was in office, or maybe under President Kennedy, I'm not sure.
   And it should have strong support.
   But I don't see any risk of backlash at all provided that you
get people that measure up, and that's what I'm trying to do.
</TEXT>
