<FIRST>r i AM-Peru     04-12 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Peru,0144</SECOND>
<UNK>Leftist Guerrillas Assassinate Governing Party Official</UNK>
<DATELINE>HUANCAYO, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Leftist guerrilla gunmen killed a leader
of the governing party's youth organization as he boarded a bus in
this highland city, police said Wednesday.
   Police blamed the Maoist Shining Path guerrilla movement for the
assassination Tuesday of Juan Torres, head of the Huancayo branch
of the Peruvian Aprista Youth.
   Two gunmen stepped from hiding and shot Torres, 21, in the head
at a bus stop one-half block from his home in Huancayo, 140 miles
east of Lima, police said.
   The Shining Path has slain dozens of officials from the
center-left Aprista Party in its nine-year insurgency to topple the
elected government and impose Marxist rule.
   Huancayo, one of the nation's most important provincial
commercial centers, has become a major focus of rebel violence over
the past three years.
</TEXT>
