<FILEID>AP-NR-04-12-89 2133EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u a AM-FamilyStabbing     04-12 0437</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Family Stabbing,0451</SECOND>
<HEAD>Four Family Members, Fetus Killed In Bloody Rampage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police have a confession but no motive for a
grisly attack that killed an entire family, including the father,
two toddlers, an expectant mother and her eight-month fetus,
officers said Wednesday.
   Newton Carlton Slawson, 34, was charged with four counts of
first-degree murder and one of manslaughter in the shooting and
stabbing deaths late Tuesday at the home of Gerald and Peggy Wood.
   ``During questioning the suspect admitted to detectives that he
killed the family members,'' police spokesman Steve Cole said in a
statement released earlier in the day. ``No clear-cut motive has
been established. ... We don't know why. We have no idea.''
   Wood, 23, was stabbed to death; his daughter, Jennifer Lynn, 4,
and son Glendon Matthew, 3, were each shot once, police said.
   Peggy Williams Wood, 21, died Wednesday following surgery at
Tampa General Hospital, about 10 hours after the 8-month-term fetus
she was carrying died at the scene, police said.
   Slawson, 34, who had worked with Wood at a compost company, was
being held without bond for a preliminary hearing Thursday.
   Police were called to the family's second-story apartment just
south of Tampa's Ybor City section shortly before 10 p.m. EDT
Tuesday, Cole said.
   Slawson, a stocky Concord, N.C., native with a clean-shaven
head, was arrested shortly after police arrived at the apartment
late Tuesday.
   They said they picked him up about 10 blocks away and recovered
a .357-caliber Magnum pistol and a six-inch folding knife from his
car.
   Slawson was living at a motel and had been visiting the couple's
home earlier in the evening, according to police. ``He went back
later and apparently committed the murders,'' Sgt. Wiley Howell
said.
   After the attack, Mrs. Wood, bleeding severely, managed to crawl
down a staircase and to her parents house next door to summon help.
   Before she was taken to a hospital, Mrs. Wood, still conscious,
told her mother that ``Newton killed her husband and children and
stabbed her,'' Detective D. Grossi said in an affidavit.
   A description of a car seen leaving the scene was broadcast on
police radio. An officer just finishing an off-duty job at a nearby
food store spotted the vehicle about 45 minutes after the killings,
Cole said.
   ``The suspect was taken into custody without incident,'' Cole
said.
   Michael Lange, manager of the Black Gold Compost Co. said
Slawson came to Florida from North Carolina late last year and
worked on a package assembly line for three weeks in February. He
quit to get a job at a fish camp, he said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
