<HEAD>UNDATED: Infectious Diseases.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   WASHINGTON _ President Bush urged a ban on campaign
contributions by political action committees and said he opposed
federal financing of congressional races Wednesday as he unveiled
proposals to tighten ethical rules for Congress, judges and the
executive branch.
   Bush announced his program in a speech to the annual convention
