<FIRST>r f PM-Sundstrand-Sony     04-12 0190</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Sundstrand-Sony,0200</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sundstrand Selling Trans Com Systems To Sony</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCKFORD, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sundstrand Corp. is selling its Trans Com
Systems to Sony USA Inc., company officials announced.
   The companies have agreed in principle on the sale, which is
subject to approval of the boards of directors of both
corporations, Sundstrand said in a statement issued.
   Terms of the sale were not disclosed.
   Trans Com, located in Costa Mesa, Calif., is a leading supplier
of airline passenger audio and visual entertainment systems. It
offers both video monitor and projection devices and is a pioneer
in the development of seatback and armrest video equipment.
   Other Trans Com products include a combination compact disc and
cassette audio system for background music and prerecorded
announcements.
   Sony has been the primary supplier of video and audio components
to Trans Com.
   Sony USA is a unit of the Japanese electronics company Sony Corp.
   Sundstrand, maker of technology-based items for the aerospace
and industrial markets, pleaded guilty in October to defrauding the
Defense Department by overbilling for aircraft parts. The company
agreed to fines and repayments totaling $177 million, the largest
settlement in Pentagon history.
</TEXT>
