<FIRST>r f BC-Transam-Criterion     04-12 0146</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Transam-Criterion,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Transamerica to Acquire Criterion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Transamerica Corp. will acquire Criterion
Group of Houston, an investment management company, for $94.3
million in cash, it was announced on Wednesday.
   Criterion Group will be operated as a separate subsidiary of
Transamerica Corp. and continue to be based in Houston, said James
Harvey, Tranamerica's chairman and chief executive officer.
   The deal expected to be completed in the third quarter of this
year is subject to the approval of Criterion's shareholders.
   Criterion operates 24 mutual funds and serves 125 separate
account clients, including corporations, labor and government
organizations. In 1988, it reported net income of $5.8 million on
revenues of $36.2 million.
   Transamerica, which provides specialized financial and insurance
services, had assets of $26.8 billion at the end of 1988. Operating
income for the year was a record $335.6 million on revenue of $7.9
billion.
</TEXT>
