<FILEID>AP-NR-04-12-89 1333EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u f BC-BritishStocks     04-12 0177</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-British Stocks,0185</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares End Slightly Higher After Losing Early Gains</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices on the London stock exchange ended slightly
higher in quiet trading Wednesday, as the market's early euphoria
wore off by the afternoon.
   Driving prices higher from the outset of trading was news that
Beecham Group and SmithKline Beckman Corp. had agreed to merge, a
move that would create the world's second largest pharmaceutical
company.
   But dealers said there wasn't sufficient retail interest to
sustain the gains and prices began heading lower at late morning.
   Nervousness ahead of Thursday's release of British employment
and average earnings data also pulled the market down, dealers
said. The figures, along with Friday's retail price statistics,
could provide further insight into the outlook for inflation.
   U.S. trade figures for February, due on Friday, also sidelined a
number of players, dealers said.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index
was up 1.7 points, or 0.08 percent, at 2,033.0.
   Volume was light, as 464.2 million shares changed hands, down
from 492.8 million shares on Tuesday.
</TEXT>
