<FILEID>AP-NR-04-12-89 1448EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Wickes-Orchard     04-12 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Wickes-Orchard,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wickes Cos. To Sell Hardware Chain for $134 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wickes Cos. announced a $134 million
deal Wednesday to sell Orchard Supply Hardware to a management
group in the latest of a series of asset sales by Wickes' new
owners.
   The buyer group is headed by Orchard Supply President Maynard
Jankins and was organized by Freeman Spogli &amp; Co., a Los Angeles
investment firm. The deal was financed by Drexel Burnham Lambert
Inc. and Bankers Trust Co.
   Wickes, a conglomerate with holdings in retailing, auto products
and wallpaper and fabrics, has been selling off assets since it was
bought last year by a partnership of Blackstone Capital Partners
and Wasserstein, Perella Partners.
   The Orchard Supply deal brings the company's gain from asset
sales to $700 million.
   The new owners are considering further sales, but intend to keep
running the company rather than breaking it up, said Jon Kutler, a
Wasserstein, Perella vice president.
   Sale of the San Jose-based hardware chain was not expected to
affect employees at Orchard Supply's 31 stores in northern and
central California, Wickes said.
</TEXT>
